cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the application of reinforcement learning (RL) to control systems, specifically in the context of dealing with external disturbances. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which encompasses RL. The paper also involves the use of abstraction techniques to extract a finite-state automaton, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with control systems and their dynamics, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
